<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>Aging in Place: How Technology Might Help You Grow Old at Home</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/22/business/seniors-home-care-tech.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/22/business/seniors-home-care-tech.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/22/business/seniors-home-care-tech.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The budding field is turning dreams into reality for older adults who are eager to age in place, filling caregiving gaps and easing minds as America ages rapidly.</description><dc:creator>Susan Shain</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 09:00:08 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Old age</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">elderly</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">senior citizens</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elderly care</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Geriatrics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Robot</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Startup</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Privacy</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">AARP</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/03/24/00caregiving-AgeTech-01-85122-cover/00caregiving-AgeTech-01-85122-cover-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image" /></item><item><title>Anthropic’s C.E.O. Says It Could Grow by 80 Times This Year</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/anthropic-ceo-ai-growth.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/anthropic-ceo-ai-growth.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/anthropic-ceo-ai-growth.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The chief executive, Dario Amodei, said the rapid growth had exponentially increased the start-up’s need for more computing power.</description><dc:creator>Natallie Rocha</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 00:39:12 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Earnings Reports</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Startup</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer Chip</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SpaceX</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Dario Amodei</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/06/multimedia/06BIZ-ANTHROPIC-mclj/06BIZ-ANTHROPIC-mclj-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Denis Balibouse/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Anthropic’s chief executive, Dario Amodei, in January. On Wednesday, he spoke at his company’s annual developer conference.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Google Says Criminal Hackers Used A.I. to Find a Major Software Flaw</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/google-hackers-attack-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/google-hackers-attack-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/google-hackers-attack-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The company said that it had identified, for the first time, hackers using artificial intelligence to discover an unknown bug. The attempted attack represents “a taste of what’s to come,” one expert said.</description><dc:creator>Dustin Volz</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 13:00:07 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Hacker (computer security)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberdefense</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberwarfare</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/11/multimedia/11dc-cyber2-fqhz/11dc-cyber2-fqhz-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Noah Berger/Associated Press</media:credit><media:description>“We have high confidence that the actor likely leveraged an A.I. model to support the discovery and weaponization of this vulnerability,” Google said in its report, published Monday.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Meditating or Rebooting? A Robot Buddhist Monk Comes to South Korea.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/robot-monk-buddhist-seoul.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/robot-monk-buddhist-seoul.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/robot-monk-buddhist-seoul.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Gabi, the newest monk at a temple in Seoul that is looking to spread Buddhism, vowed to not overcharge as it seeks enlightenment.</description><dc:creator>Remy Tumin and John Yoon</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 21:21:45 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Buddhism</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Monasteries</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Jogye</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Robot</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Seoul</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/06/world/asia/2026-05-06T054951Z_2010695814_RC2H3LARFX6Z_RTRMADP_3_SOUTHKOREA-ROBOT-MONK/2026-05-06T054951Z_2010695814_RC2H3LARFX6Z_RTRMADP_3_SOUTHKOREA-ROBOT-MONK-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Yonhap News Agency, via via Reuters</media:credit></media:content></item></channel></rss>